news.title: Chennai metro rail to begin land acquisition for Coimbatore metro project
news.para: M A Siddique, managing director, CMRL, said they were hopeful that the Union govt would approve the metro rail projects in Coimbatore and Madurai soon.

news.title: Doctor duped of Rs 70 lakh in flat purchase deal in Navi Mumbai
news.para: The accused showed a flat located in Roadpali area of Kalamboli to the doctor and expressed their intention to sell it to him despite the fact that it had been already sold to someone else.

news.title: Mumbai Metro One lenders in talks to sell Rs 1,226-crore debt to NARCL
news.para: The National Asset Reconstruction Company (NARCL) has offered ₹1,063 crore to acquire Mumbai Metro One (MMOPL)'s principal outstanding debt of ₹1,226 crore, the people said.

news.title: Pune: Collectorate gets advanced system to track illegal sand mining
news.para: The pilot project, launched last month, enables real-time monitoring of sand-mining activities across 200 locations throughout the district. The office features an advanced surveillance system that includes GPS tracking of vehicles involved in sand transportation.

news.title: Odisha govt asks civic bodies to invite applications for PM housing scheme for urban areas
news.para: Odisha Urban Housing Mission (OUHM) under the Housing & Urban Development Department has issued an instruction to the civic bodies to this effect.

news.title: PE investments in Indian real estate rise 10% to $4.3 billion in 2024: Savills India
news.para: Foreign institutional investors accounted for 88% of the total investment activity in 2024, reinforcing their dominant role in driving growth in the sector.

news.title: N Srinivasan, other promoters steps down from India Cements' board
news.para: The Aditya Birla Group firm has completed the acquisition of 10.13 crore equity shares of India Cements Ltd (ICL), representing 32.72 per cent of the equity share capital of the company.

news.title: Prime minister to launch 58 lakh property cards under SVAMITVA
news.para: SVAMITVA Scheme, which was launched in 2020, aims at providing a "Record of Rights" to every property owner in the Village Abadi area.

news.title: Nearly 77% realization of recovery certificates issued by UP-RERA in Ghaziabad
news.para: According to data from the board of revenue, Ghaziabad has a 23% pendency rate, while GB Nagar has 72% and Varanasi has 94%.

news.title: IBM in advance talks with TRIL to lease 2.6 lakh sq ft office space in Gurugram
news.para: Absorption of Grade A office space was hitherto led by the return-to-office routine for major technology companies, but several other demand drivers are expected to help sustain the momentum.

news.title: 2024 round-up: Strong first half keeps housing sales momentum intact
news.para: ​​Average housing prices across the top eight cities have already surged 11% annually in 2024. Interestingly, with rising cost pressures, affordability issues can impact the segment more as compared to the office and industrial & warehousing segments.

news.title: Indian real estate: A catalyst for economic development
news.para: A combination of factors, including urbanization and a stable interest rate regime, has fueled strong demand across residential and commercial real estate segments. The sector's growth is driven by diverse real estate asset classes, offering opportunities for domestic and international investors.

news.title: Mohali civic body survey reveals 97 illegal high-rises in city
news.para: Regarding unauthorised shops in villages under the MC, the mayor held an emergency meeting with MC commissioner T Benith and building branch and fire department officials.

news.title: Delhi civic body mandates immediate registration of construction workers for welfare benefits
news.para: "Accordingly, we issued directions to all execution engineers in the building departments of 12 zones to contact the empanelled project contractors engaged in construction work, including our projects, and assist their workers in getting enrolled on the website at the earliest," the official said.

news.title: KCB sends plan to merge 326 acres in civilian areas with Pune civic body
news.para: The move came after consultations with Southern Command, the local military authority, Bombay Engineering Group and Centre, and Ammunition Factory Khadki.

news.title: Lucknow civic body to launch new app for self-assessment of properties soon
news.para: To facilitate this upgrade and resolve technical issues, the existing web-based service has been temporarily suspended for 15 days. The suspension aims to address ongoing technical glitches and improve security features for both the app and the website.

news.title: Gurugram metro construction to begin on May 1, 2025: Haryana CM
news.para: The metro line, spanning 28.5km, will have 27 stations. The corridor will be launched with three coaches per train and will be increased to six coaches later.

news.title: Bengaluru: Land acquisition begins for Namma metro phase III
news.para: The notification was issued for acquiring 26,811 sqm of land to build an elevated line and Metro stations between JP Nagar 4th Phase and Mysuru Road station.

news.title: Assam CM announces 300 crore residential colony in AMCH
news.para: With an estimated investment of Rs 300 crore, the project aims to provide a significant boost to medical infrastructure in upper Assam.
